Back down memory lane
“Hey dad, can you take a picture of me over there??” 😅🤳🌺

I vanished for a couple of months, and now I want to return here with transparency…

While my online presence was on hold, my mother’s journey is continuing, and I want to tell it from the daughters point of view. I took a break from social media to fully engage with my family and construct my own life. It took me a while to genuinely value what we have and all the moments worth cherishing. Change was sweeping through every aspect of my life, and I found myself holding on by a thread. 

As I navigate my twenties, I’m constructing the life I aspire to have, and time is what I’ve feared and appreciated. However, accepting uncertainty and living presently has been what I’ve been holding onto. It’s not easy and Im happy to share that journey on this platform to shine light for anyone else who may be going through this. My mother is a fighter and continues to be. 

Our focus now is on living in the present, embracing each day as a gift. #cancerawareness #healing #healthjourney
I’m a better person outside 🪴

Whatever floats your boat 🌊

Reflection Reminds Us Of What Truly Matters 👇🏼🤍

I hope everyone’s weekend is ending off nicely!

As my Sunday evening comes to a close, wanted to take some time to reflect as I’m diving more into journaling 📜

The Backstory:
When I first tackled teaching, being a student, and diving into social media, it felt like navigating a maze. Juggling all these roles, I stumbled through trial and error. Where I was not forgive myself or situation in my life. Life wasn’t perfect, but I discovered that acknowledging the hiccups was key to improvement. Embracing the journey from humble beginnings, I realized that discomfort was a signal for change. Through these experiences, I learned that the bumps in the road are lessons, guiding me toward a more authentic and fulfilling life. As we go to the next chapter it’s always good to reflect on the good and the bad. As I go to my wounded past I shift my perspective in how much I’m grateful for those situation. It put me into better perspective quicker in my life and clear my mind of burden. 

Overall, I wanted you to know that the journey your in right now will only make you stronger than yesterday, keep going! It’s a tough battle. Forgive your past and appreciate it for shaping you into a stronger individual 🤍

Reading to grow ☁️📚

Here is my lil review: ✨

This book has improved my way of thinking so much and expanded my mindset. It has a great variety of life topics. It’s so relevant to today’s world. It brings comfort but also challenges you and the way you think. Today’s society makes us feel like we have to have the perfect life and do everything and be everything just to feel allowed to feel happy and that’s part of the reason I love this book, it challenges the way you think about that unrealistic beliefs and more. Some of my favorite chapters are “How to measure a good life” “102 ways to not let irrational thoughts ruin your life” and “How to stop worrying about how your life looks and start focusing on how it feels”. I think it’s beneficial to anyone who reads it.

The truth is.. working out is dreadful. 👇🏼

But it’s a form of respect for yourself

It’s showing up for yourself and giving THANKS that you can do the things you do.

As a woman we aren’t grown up to lifting weights and it being “abnormal”. I’m the complete opposite because it helped fix my lower back problems and made me a stronger dancer. There are more benefits than being scared of looking bulky.. which lifting isn’t the reason ❌
